  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="KT42-kilavi">iravukkuṟi vēṇṭiya kiḻavaṟkut tōḻi nērnta vāyppaṭṭāṉ maṟuttatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">The confidante refusing HIM who wished for night trysts, while granting by implication.</p>
          </div>



        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="KT42">
<l>                kāma moḻiva tāyiṉum yāmattuk</l>
<l>                karuvi māmaḻai vīḻnteṉa varuvi</l>
<l>                viṭarakat tiyampu nāṭaven</l>
<l>                toṭarpun tēyumō niṉvayi ṉāṉē.</l>

             </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
             <l>Even if desire is passing,<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">oḻivatu</term> as a form is ambiguous, that is, either finite verb or participial noun. If the latter, then the nuance might rather be attributive and general: "even if desire is transitory ...".</note>man of the mountains</l>  
             <l rend="indent">where inside a cave the waterfall is sounding</l>
             <l rend="indent">because so much rain has fallen at midnight</l>
             <l>
               <choice> 
                <seg>does our attachment dwindle, too, on your side?</seg>
                <seg>– does our attachment dwindle, too? I [am] with you.<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">nāṉ</term>: cf. note on KT 36.6.</note></seg>
             </choice>
            </l>

                
                </lg>
